 class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_7424528\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_7424528\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wrk1719679878225.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wrk1719679878225.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wrk1719679878225.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hff1665702734111\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Database Access on SQLite\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The SLE connector uses the embedded SQLite library to access and manipulate the DBMS file.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hff1665702734111__section_w2063ab1b5b1_w2064ab1b5_w2065ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hff1665702734111__section_w2066ab1b5b3_w2067ab1b5_w2068ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d611268e56\">\n                        \n Database Path\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hff1665702734111__p_d58712e1_d58713e1_d58714e1\">Specify the logon path for the connector as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$SLE SLE:<var class=\"keyword varname\">database</var> </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hff1665702734111__p_d58715e1_d58716e1_d58717e1\">where <var class=\"keyword varname\">database</var> is a file path assignment, possibly containing Uniface path logicals. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$SLE SLE: C:/Uniface_Data/project/dbms/usys.db</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hff1665702734111__p_d58718e1_d58719e1_d58720e1\">The SLE connector does not check for a user name or password.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hff1665702734111__section_w2069ab1b5b5_w2070ab1b5_w2071ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d611268e84\">\n                        \n Using SQLite for the Repository\n </h2>\n<div class=\"note important note_important\" id=\"hff1665702734111__note_w2075ab1b5b5b3_w2076ab1b5b5_w2077ab1b5_w2078ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Important:</span> SQLite can be used as Repository in a stand-alone environment. It should not be used as a shared Repository.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hff1665702734111__p_d58724e1_d58725e1_d58726e1\">When used as a Repository, the Uniface system information assignments $IDF, $UUU, $SYS and $DEF can all be assigned to the SLE connector. For example, the following is a typical</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hff1665702734111__p_d58727e1_d58728e1_d58729e1\">$IDF is the assignment for the Repository. If SQLite is used, it is advisable to create at least a four MB application database to hold the application definition and the data.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"hff1665702734111__section_evl_ltz_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d611268e99\">Example: Basic Configuration </h2>\n<p class=\"p\">SQLite is the installed as the default database on Windows, using the\n            following configuration in the assignment file.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"hff1665702734111__pre_wp1_mtz_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[DRIVER_SETTINGS]\nSLE U2.0\nUSYS$SLE_PARAMS create db = on\n[PATHS]\n; Path to the SQLite database for the Uniface Repository:\n$DBMS SLE:<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceDataFolder</var>/project/dbms/usys.db\n; Path to the SQLite database for User defined data:\n$DBMS_DEF SLE:<var class=\"keyword varname\">UnifaceDataFolder</var>/project/dbms/userdata.db\n$SYS $DBMS\n$UUU $DBMS\n$IDF $DBMS\n$DEF $DBMS_DEF\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bsx1723125799922.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>create db</a><p>If the database file does not yet exist, creates a database file in the path specified by the connector setting.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7424528\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_7424528\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Database Access on SQLite Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Database Access on SQLite The SLE connector uses the embedded SQLite library to access and manipulate the DBMS file. Database Path Specify the logon path for the connector as follows: $SLE SLE: database Copy where database is a file path assignment, possibly containing Uniface path logicals. For example: $SLE SLE: C:/Uniface_Data/project/dbms/usys.db Copy The SLE connector does not check for a user name or password. Using SQLite for the Repository Important: SQLite can be used as Repository in a stand-alone environment. It should not be used as a shared Repository. When used as a Repository, the Uniface system information assignments $IDF, $UUU, $SYS and $DEF can all be assigned to the SLE connector. For example, the following is a typical $IDF is the assignment for the Repository. If SQLite is used, it is advisable to create at least a four MB application database to hold the application definition and the data. Example: Basic Configuration SQLite is the installed as the default database on Windows, using the following configuration in the assignment file. [DRIVER_SETTINGS] SLE U2.0 USYS$SLE_PARAMS create db = on [PATHS] ; Path to the SQLite database for the Uniface Repository: $DBMS SLE: UnifaceDataFolder /project/dbms/usys.db ; Path to the SQLite database for User defined data: $DBMS_DEF SLE: UnifaceDataFolder /project/dbms/userdata.db $SYS $DBMS $UUU $DBMS $IDF $DBMS $DEF $DBMS_DEF Copy Related Links create db If the database file does not yet exist, creates a database file in the path specified by the connector setting. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}